Catch me on this weeks podcast episode of #BrownLove by @contodonetflix with the amazing @sheisdash 
I wanted to take a moment share how special I felt to sit with you Dascha💕 not only because I admire and follow your work but I felt so at ease talking with you boo. Thanks for being an amazing and talented Latina in the industry and inviting me to share this moment with you. Also thanks to @contodonetflix for creating a show that highlights the work of fellow Latinx people in the industry we appreciate this 👏🏽

I’m so honored to make part of @camila_cabello new music video and single “Don’t Go Yet” Out Now, check it out! 

A very big special thanks to Camila and her amazing team, everyone in production, the directors @pilar_zeta and @original_xerox for having me, the sweetest choreographers @calvitjr and @sarabiv , all the dancers, @lisa_tv for serving it up in the fashion department, @sethpratt for my custom dress and my the biggest thanks to my home girl @walliecruz who did an amazing job doing my hair for both looks!

Hello it’s me... Valentina! 

I would love to shout out my friends who came through to create and play Barbie with me. I got the call to be on @rupaulsdragrace latest season for a Miss Congeniality Roast along side @heidincloset @ninawest while I was in Guadalajara visiting my friends and I said yes. In the times of covid I was staying over at my friends @victor_olmos_ and @alidanielflores of @olmosyflores where they have a studio where we spent hours creating this one of a kind labor of love. We as friends/artist are always inspired by our motherland Mexico. We wanted to show the vibrant colors and textures of the country. And I asked myself “what would María Félix wear?” I truly enjoyed every second and all the love that went into creating this one of a kind work of art made by my talented friends. This gown consist of three parts which are a high waisted mermaid tail skirt, a black lace undergarment with built in garter belt and a highly structured bustier top. All of which were styled with custom gloves black ultra high opera length glove by @wingweftgloves and accessorized with the ever classic thick Latina hoop earring. 

For hair and makeup @hisvintagetouch @shablamgela @ernestocasillas we wanted to explore black hair cause of the María Félix reference and of course the black undergarments and gloves. When it came to makeup up Shablam and I wanted to play with a skinny brow and experiment with this idea of the new 20’s. También muchas gracias a mi amiga @rickylips por regalarme sus hips pads para este look. I love you all and I hope you enjoyed a little back story to this labor of love.

node.text:
I’ve been holding off from making this post for a while now but today’s the day. This little spirit here is my baby, who I love with all of my heart. His name is Monchi, I also call him Monchuchu and when he’s an older I’m gonna call him Don Ramon. He’s a bi color Persian cat with a peke face and requires lots of pampering and grooming. Just like his mother, he loves glamour and long naps. I have to brush him every day, clean his eyes and even put a white powder on his eyes called @eyeenvytearstains which is like make-up for cats. My baby has the best kitty healthcare and vet at @mohawkalleyvets and gets groomed at a place called @cateaumarmont He smells like oatmeal and looks like a cross between a bunny rabbit and an Ewok from Star Wars.
I love him soooo much,
He’s my first pet and I’m so happy to introduce you all to my little baby. 

Also here I’m wearing a custom sparkle dress by my friend @aidan.euan who I wanted to congratulate on his most recent feature in @voguemexico congrats boo!

node.text:
At the time of this portrait I was living in Echo Park, recently laid off from Prada. This photo was taken for my audition package for @rupaulsdragrace At the time I had been doing drag for a short amount of time, doing $50 gigs for fun and living my fantasy of taking 8 hours to get into drag for any local opportunity I could get. I had won a Halloween Dragula witch ball pageant with the @bouletbrothers, I tried out for project drag @mickysweho and I got denied,  I was crushed but saw a glimmer of hope when @martabeatchu @saintpeterdvil and @theonlymayhem were the first queens to hire me. Back then I was so excited and in love with the art of drag and wanted to learn how to beat my mug like @itsravenhunty_  and I would study her face every Monday night at Showgirls. And now home gurl paints @rupaulofficial ! I was always super extra would arrive to all my gigs in a trench coat, heels, a silk scarf tied around my head and perfumed the haus down boots tongue pop mawma werq. Soooo much has happened since this portrait taken by my Amiga @abelr and I guess I wanted to take some time to reflect and share this with you all just because. Maybe it can help motivate someone to never give up on your dreams. Thank you to all those of you who have been a part of this journey with me. 
It’s been a crazy magical ride but it’s just getting started! Besos 😘

We’re teaming up with @unileverusa, @whenweallvote & the legendary Houses of Balenciaga, Garcon, Gorgeous Gucci and Miyake-Mugler to turn the vote out.

Election day is November 3 and it’s gonna get severe up in here, y’all! Here’s the tea: 1 in 5 LGBTQ+ eligible voters aren’t registered to vote. When we show up we bring our experiences, giving voice to issues that impact our community.  We are all the vote!

There are three simple steps to show up! Watch the film and let icon @siniabraxton show you how.

Gag the nation with your voice loudly by registering to vote at WWW.WEALL.VOTE/IMTHEVOTE or text IMTHEVOTE TO 26797. Stand up for your right to vote and make it count — you’re the vote! #imthevote #UnileverUSApartner #RanaVerse
